      "writtenOn": "2018-06-29T18:39:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "SkPngCodec doesn\u0027t completely support incremental decoding. Although it does implement the methods, and they are used in SkSampledCodec (which is used by Android to decoded a sampled version of the image without ever allocating space for the entire image), it doesn\u0027t work for the case where the data is supplied incrementally (which is crucial for Chromium). The following document sums up \"incremental decoding\":\n\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/11Mn8-ePDKwVEMCjs3nWwSjxcSpJ_Cu8DF57KNtUmgLM/\n\nSkPngCodec needs to buffer the incoming data somehow, in case we had less than a whole chunk of data to decode. The plan is to use SkStreamBuffer for that purpose.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 22,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 26,
        "endChar": 45
      },
