      "writtenOn": "2018-07-28T06:21:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You say it\u0027s taken care of by the base class, but in my newer patch set, I still need to explicitly zero-initialize, or else the AnimatedImage test fails on images/alphabetAnim.gif. Am I holding something wrong?\n\nThat might just mean that I\u0027m not setting *rowsDecoded properly, in my newer patch set. I\u0027m not sure if that\u0027s plausible, though, because the part of the image that\u0027s outside the frame isn\u0027t just complete rows. It can be part-rows, if the frame left-and-width isn\u0027t the same as 0-and-the-image-width. Does that make sense??",
