      "writtenOn": "2018-06-29T18:39:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We do have SkStream::getMemoryBase(). If that returns non-null, we can store it and the length in an SkData. SkWebpCodec already does this. (If getMemoryBase returns null, it just copies the whole stream, since libwebp requires a consecutive block of memory. I\u0027ve been thinking that Android should just always give us the whole block, which would make this easier. It doesn\u0027t help the incremental case, though.)",
